<span id="freeTextContainer16079166185799629908">I have enjoyed the Cadfael series from the start, but some of the first books didn&apos;t quite hit the mark for me. his book however is an excellent murder mystery with the wry asides and great historical details I enjoyed in the first books. Peters has managed to combine the detective ingenuity of Hercule Poirot with the humour of Morse in a historical setting as vividly written as any I have read.</span>
  <span id="freeText16079166185799629908" style="display:none">I have enjoyed the Cadfael series from the start, but some of the first books didn't quite hit the mark for me. his book however is an excellent murder mystery with the wry asides and great historical details I enjoyed in the first books. Peters has managed to combine the detective ingenuity of Hercule Poirot with the humour of Morse in a historical setting as vividly written as any I have read.</span>
